body:
Why is this not integrated? Currently working around it, by extending DBCache and encapsulating overwritten <code>setValue()</code> content in:
```php
protected function setValue($key, $value, $duration)
{
	if ($this->db->enableQueryCache) {
		// temporarily disable and re-enable query caching
		$this->db->enableQueryCache = false;
		parent::setValue($key, $value, $duration);
		$this->db->enableQueryCache = true;
	} else {
		parent::setValue($key, $value, $duration);
	}
}
```
Most other methods of DBCache use <code>$this->db->enableQueryCache</code> as this, I guess for the exact same reason.
